\v 13 I reckoned till morning, \add that,\add* as a lion, so will he break all
my bones: from day \add even\add* to night wilt thou make an end of me. 
\v 14 Like a crane \add or\add* a swallow, so did I chatter: I did mourn as a
dove: mine eyes fail \add with looking\add* upward: O LORD, I am oppressed;
